!!! Note from a native Romanian:

While I do appreciate you showcasing the beauty of our country and it's wild areas, please keep in mind that this country is NOT perfect or as picturesque as you present it here.

The main problem with Romania is its people. The majority of the population is wildly uneducated and close-minded. Mainly due to a lack of access to free education and due to the indoctrination of the people by the church.

Our political system is very corrupt, and even though the general population is not happy with it, they more often than not choose the same people to lead them because of their lack of political education. It's a country full of racists, sexists, homophobes, transphobes, xenophobes, and whatnot. Even people with higher education can turn out to be very close-minded.

It's easy to present this country as being welcoming and beautiful from the perspective of a white cis-gendered person. But it's a completely different story for any other kind of person that visits or lives here.

The natives will try to make a good first impression with tourists at first, but don't be fooled by that. That warmth ends the second that you don't adhere to their traditional norms.


While I'm NOT saying that you shouldn't visit Romania, just be wary of its people. They can be deceiving.

Sincerely,
A Romanian who has lost faith in his country.

P.S. I will not respond to any natives that will try to mindlessly ignore these aspects. This is an honest view of this country.
